http://www.avn.info.ve/contenido/maduro-and-santos-meet-puerto-ayacucho^Maduro and Santos meet in Puerto Ayacucho | AVN^NA^20130723095031^0.11296178^828e11288935dddf81287cf8138895b9^0.042806376^2013-07-23T12:55:35.756Z^http://www.avn.info.ve/contenido/maduro-and-santos-meet-puerto-ayacucho^"Maduro and Santos meet in Puerto Ayacucho | AVN English Maduro and Santos meet in Puerto Ayacucho &nbsp; Caracas, 22 Jul. AVN.- The presidents of Venezuela and Colombia, Nicolas Maduro and Juan Manuel Santos, are already meeting in the Army Brigade number 7, in Puerto Ayacucho, southern state of Amazonas. The state-run channel Venezolana de Television showed pictures from the private meeting held by the two leaders. After this meeting there will be an extended meeting, which will include issues such as border security, trade, fight against smuggling and the peace process with the FARC (Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia). At the end of this meeting, an official statement will be made, reported Colombian newspaper El Tiempo. Maduro and Santos meet after the Colombian president received last May former presidential candidate of the Venezuelan right, Henrique Capriles, who ignored the results of the presidential election on April 14. After ignoring the popular will, Capriles called his followers to go to the headquarters of the National Electoral Council (CNE) across the country, a move that eventually turned into violence that caused the death of 11 people who were on the streets celebrating the victory of the Bolivarian Revolution. After a few months, Maduro and Santos have said to set back the rules of the game that allows them to continue to have a stable bilateral relationship. &nbsp; AVN 22/07/2013 17:00 English Meeting of CELAC ministers starts in Caracas English Defense Minister: Armed forces committed to defend the homeland English Movements marched to eradicate hunger, poverty Special Reports Mandela's long walk Rayuela, 50 years of eternal youth Headlines 17.00 Maduro