http://www.avn.info.ve/contenido/meeting-celac-ministers-starts-caracas^Meeting of CELAC ministers starts in Caracas | AVN^NA^20130723095031^0.11296178^bfef547c59bc687749d82573c7f0ba9d^0.042799022^2013-07-23T13:55:44.911Z^http://www.avn.info.ve/contenido/meeting-celac-ministers-starts-caracas^"Meeting of CELAC ministers starts in Caracas | AVN English Meeting of CELAC ministers starts in Caracas &nbsp; Caracas, 22 Jul. AVN.- The meeting of social ministers of the Community of Latin American and Caribbean States started Monday with a recorded speech of late leader of Bolivarian Revolution Hugo Chavez. In the video, the former Venezuelan president emphasized the importance of CELAC, a new tool of integration that unites American countries without meddling of the United States or Canada. In that speech to open CELAC, Hugo Chavez requested to prevent that intrigues spoiled this new effort of integration. In the meeting in Caracas, social ministers are expected to tackle with different issues to achieve development, eliminate poverty and inequalities in American and Caribbean countries. The event, held at Catia theater in Caracas, is attended by Venezuelan vice-president for the social area, Hector Rodriguez, who is expected to propose to extend social programs Robinson (literacy) and Milagro (visual health) to Latin America and the Caribbean. AVN 22/07/2013 12:37 English Maduro and Santos meet in Puerto Ayacucho English Defense Minister: Armed forces committed to defend the homeland English Movements marched to eradicate hunger, poverty Special Reports Mandela's long walk Rayuela, 50 years of eternal youth Headlines 17.00 Maduro and Santos meet in Puerto Ayacucho 16.36 Meeting between Maduro and Santos to resume bilateral agenda 14.33 Movements marched to eradicate hunger, poverty 12.53 We aim to structurally reduce crime by 40% by 2019 12.37 Meeting of CELAC ministers starts in Caracas See more Noticias Multimedia SIBCI ULAN Aliados Poder Popular Caracas Fotografía Cor