http://www.avn.info.ve/contenido/defense-minister-armed-forces-committed-defend-homeland^Defense Minister: Armed forces committed to defend the homeland | AVN^NA^20130723095031^0.09413482^8d6f4675c1278bb02aa53ec443ace081^0.03765804^2013-07-23T13:58:36.184Z^http://www.avn.info.ve/contenido/defense-minister-armed-forces-committed-defend-homeland^"Defense Minister: Armed forces committed to defend the homeland | AVN English Defense Minister: Armed forces committed to defend the homeland &nbsp; Caracas, 22 Jul. AVN.- Venezuela's Bolivarian National Armed Force is united, strengthened and committed to defend the homeland before any aggression or conspiracy, said Defense minister Carmen Melendez. Interviewed in local television on Sunday, she said these last years have been marked by conspiracy but not within Armed Forces, but against supply. Also, they have speculated with medicines, electricity. There have been staged conspiracies to destabilize the country. They are there, lying in wait, but they have not made it. The Defense minister affirmed that the Armed Forces will do as much as possible so that not any fire is caught. We will be on the alert. As a matter of fact, she affirmed there will not be another coup as that on April 11, 2002. I think within the institution will not occur what happen on April 11. That's impossible. We have Armed Forces and its high command committed to the homeland, to defend the homeland. Someone may want to go against people, but we will be there alert to answer immediately, Carmen Melendez added. AVN 22/07/2013 10:26 English Maduro and Santos meet in Puerto Ayacucho English Meeting of CELAC ministers starts in Caracas English Movements marched to eradicate hunger, poverty Special Reports Mandela's long walk Rayuela, 50 years of eternal youth Headlines 17.00 Maduro and Santos meet in Puerto Ayacucho 16.36 Meeting between Maduro and Santos to resume bilateral agenda 14.33 Movements marched to eradicate hunger, poverty 12.53 We aim to struc